The purpose of the research is to better understand why people might prefer a certain politician over another one. The survey will ask you some questions about yourself, about your political attitudes, and about your reaction to different hypothetical politicians. It should take approximately 10 minutes to complete.
 Your responses are anonymous, and there are not likely to be any risks or discomforts associated with your participation in the survey. The research team works to ensure confidentiality to the degree permitted by technology. It is possible, although unlikely, that unauthorized individuals could gain access to your responses because you are responding online. However, your participation in this online survey involves risks similar to a person’s everyday use of the internet. If you have concerns, you should consult the survey provider privacy policy here. Your MechanicalTurk Worker ID will be used to distribute payment to you, but will not be stored with the research data we collect from you. Please be aware that your MTurk Worker ID can potentially be linked to information about you on your Amazon public profile page, depending on the settings you have for your Amazon profile. We will not be accessing any personally identifying information about you that you may have put on your Amazon public profile page. Respondents to this survey will be paid $1.81 via MTurk. For questions about the study, the principal investigator (Prof. Cole Harvey) can be reached at cole.j.harvey@okstate.edu. The Institutional Review Board at Oklahoma State University can be reached at irb@okstate.edu for questions about the rights of participants. If you are uncomfortable answering any question, you may skip it. You may also discontinue the survey without penalty. Respondents must be 18 years old or older to participate in the study.
